{"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"EditorInspector","kind":"identifier"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"overview","type":"heading","text":"Overview","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This is the control that implements property editing in the editor’s Settings dialogs, the Inspector dock, etc. To get the "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorInspector"},{"text":" used in the editor’s Inspector dock, use ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorInterface\/getInspector()"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorInspector","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" will show properties in the same order as the array returned by "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Object\/getPropertyList()","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If a property’s name is path-like (i.e. if it contains forward slashes), "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorInspector"},{"type":"text","text":" will create nested sections for “directories” along the path. For example, if a property is named "},{"code":"highlighting\/gdscript\/node_path_color","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", it will be shown as “Node Path Color” inside the “GDScript” section nested inside the “Highlighting” section."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If a property has ","type":"text"},{"code":"PropertyUsageFlags\/propertyUsageGroup","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" usage, it will group subsequent properties whose name starts with the property’s hint string. The group ends when a property does not start with that hint string or when a new group starts. An empty group name effectively ends the current group. "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorInspector"},{"type":"text","text":" will create a top-level section for each group. For example, if a property with group usage is named "},{"code":"Collide With","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and its hint string is "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"collide_with_"},{"text":", a subsequent ","type":"text"},{"code":"collide_with_area","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" property will be shown as “Area” inside the “Collide With” section. There is also a special case: when the hint string contains the name of a property, that property is grouped too. This is mainly to help grouping properties like ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"font"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"font_color"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"font_size"},{"type":"text","text":" (using the hint string "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"font_"},{"text":").","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If a property has "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PropertyUsageFlags\/propertyUsageSubgroup"},{"type":"text","text":" usage, a subgroup will be created in the same way as a group, and a second-level section will be created for each subgroup."}]},{"style":"note","name":"Note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Unlike sections created from path-like property names, "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorInspector","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" won’t capitalize the name for sections created from groups. So properties with group usage usually use capitalized names instead of snake_cased names."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"aside"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This object emits the following signals:","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorInspector\/propertySelected","isActive":true,"type":"reference"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorInspector\/propertyKeyed"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorInspector\/propertyDeleted"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorInspector\/resourceSelected"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorInspector\/objectIdSelected"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorInspector\/propertyEdited"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorInspector\/propertyToggled"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorInspector\/editedObjectChanged"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorInspector\/restartRequested"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot"]]},"relationshipsSections":[{"identifiers":["do